<BaseLayout title="Start Here" description="Begin with The Yes-Way: a practical philosophy of self-mastery in service of others.">
  <section class="page-intro about-intro reveal is-visible">
    <div><h1>Start here.</h1><p>The Yes-Way is a practical philosophy of self-mastery in service of others.</p></div>
    <Emblem size={150} />
  </section>
  <article class="prose about-prose reveal">
    <p class="lead">One idea sits underneath everything here: <strong>you get strong by learning from and helping others.</strong> Strength is trained in private and spent in public. Self-mastery is the means. Service is the point.</p>
    <h2>A surname that is also a thesis.</h2>
    <p>My family name is Iesue. Most people read it as <em>Issue</em>. Said properly, it sounds like <em>yes way</em>.</p>
    <p>An issue is what life hands you. The Yes-Way is what you do about it: affirm reality, choose responsibility, build the strength to serve, and keep walking the path.</p>
    <blockquote>Strength to serve. Service to grow.</blockquote>
    <h2>What you will find here</h2>
    <p>The publication has five forms. Numbered <strong>Iesues</strong> are substantial, sourced essays that develop an enduring argument. <strong>Practical Notes</strong> turn an idea into something immediately usable. <strong>Seminar Notes</strong> frame a question for teaching and serious discussion. <strong>Case Notes</strong> examine a consequential decision in context. <strong>Marginalia</strong> records a compact, cited encounter with another thinker’s work.</p>
    <p>Together they explore leadership, learning, entrepreneurship, organizational life, and the disciplines that make contribution possible.</p>
    <p><a class="text-link" href="https://josephiesue.com/yes-way/">Read the full canon <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></p>
  </article>
  <Subscribe />
